They spend a little more, OK?

00:34:36.469 --> 00:34:39.620
Maybe, a night a week,
they can get shelter, OK?

00:34:39.620 --> 00:34:41.719
So, basically,
that's what they do.

00:34:41.719 --> 00:34:44.197
That's their constrained
optimization.

00:34:44.197 --> 00:34:45.739
We're not saying
it's right or wrong.

00:34:45.739 --> 00:34:47.072
This is not normative economics.

00:34:47.072 --> 00:34:48.350
It's positive.

00:34:48.350 --> 00:34:50.750
The positive thing is, given
